    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-08T23:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-08T23:00:00-05:00" n="571"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d571">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1121 Smit, Albert H./14: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-09T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 9, 1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received March 9—6:32 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Following from Minister Johnson dated Shanghai, March 8, 2 p.m.: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Please repeat the following to the Department: ‘Your 84, March 4, 7
                                p.m.<note n="10" xml:id="d571fn1">Not printed.</note> I share the
                            feeling of the District Attorney that the investigation should proceed,
                            and recommend that requisition of funds be arranged as outlined in
                            Porter’s telegram of March 3, 4 p.m.,<note n="10" xml:id="d571fn2">Not
                                printed.</note> it being desirable (1) that all evidence should be
                            before the district attorney for the purpose of determining whether
                            there is any basis for criminal prosecution and (2) in order to show
                            that a thorough investigation has been made’”.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
